Programs = Algorithms + Data Structures



The key to solving many algorithmic problems is to think of them in terms of graphs... it is amazing how often messy applied problems have a simple description and solution in terms of classical graph properties Skiena 2008.




0. Propaedeutic
1. Graph representation
2. Graph exploration
3. Optimization problems: MST, shortest paths, maximum flow
4. Hard problems, e.g. graph isomorphisms
5. A catalog of graph algorithms





